Pumpkin Baked Oatmeal
  --MinimalistBaker
  
2 flax eggs
1/3 c pumpkin puree (unsweetened)
1/4 c maple syrup
1 1/2 tsp pumpkin spice
1/2 tsp cinnamon
2 c df milk
2 1/2 c gf rolled oats
3/4 c chopped pecans (or nut of choice)
1/3 c fresh or frozen cranberries (or other fruit) optional
1-2 tbsp coconut sugar (optional)

Preheat oven to 350F/176C and grease a 2 qt baking dish with oil. Prepare flax eggs in a large mixing bowl. Then add pumpkin, syrup, oil, salt, spices, and whisk to combine. Add milk and stir once more. Then add oats and pecans and stir to combine. Transfer mixture to prepared dish and top with additional pecans. Sprinkle with coconut sugar (if using) and cranberries (if using). Bake for 30-35 min or until the top is golden brown, the edges are slightly caramelized, and it has some springiness in the center. Let cool a few minutes. Serve warm with desired toppings, such as coconut whipped cream, warmed coconut milk, drizzle of maple syrup, etc. Store leftovers in refrigerator 3-4 days or in freezer up to 1 month.

Notes: flax egg = 1 tbsp flax meal + 2 1/2 tbsp water, mix and let stand for 5 min.
       Can combine everything and refrigerate overnight, then bake in the morning. 
       

Pumpkin Spice:
1 tbsp cinnamon
2 tsp ground ginger
1/2 tsp allspice
1/2 tsp ground cloves
1/2 tsp ground mace
1/2 tsp ground nutmeg

Whisk to combine. Store in an airtight container for up to 1 yr.
